rComments: This course builds and excellent foundation for learning Arabic language and Prof Blackburn was instrumental in making sure this solid foundation was laid for students who wish to advance further in Arabic and Islamic studies in general and especially if they are looking to teach Arabic or any language in future themselves. Thanks Prof. Blackburn!

If you're interested in a mediocre history education then Blackburn is the way to go. As noted below he makes an interesting subject really boring. He reads his lectures and this ruins any chance for class discussion.He should stick to language classes.
This course was extremely challenging, but the professor made it do-able!   You had to work to succeed, but those who lasted learned so much!  Great teacher for a very difficult subject!

About the prof: This individual knows his stuff inside-out.  He's one of those prof's who don't give a damn about anyone else. His lectures are extremely boring.  A hard marker and a real irritating and uninteresting character.  Would not recommend at all
